<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> sell someone down the river • send someone down the river</xh5><p> <i>sell someone down the river</i>—(coll.) let a person down; betray smb.: It’s my considered opinion, John, we’ve been <u>sold down the river</u>.</p><p> <i>send someone down the river</i>—(coll., also: send someone down) send a person to prison: He had overheard Miss Jones threatening Mr. Dee “to <u>send him down the river</u> for life.”</p><p> <i>See also: row someone up Salt River / send someone up the river.</i></p> </entry>
